(16806, 'spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Acetylsalicylic Acid Acetylsalicylic acid may reduce the efficacy of spironolactone. Therefore, when spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide tablets and acetylsalicylic acid are used concomitantly, spironolactone and hydrochlorothiazide tablets may need to be titrated to higher maintenance dose and the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect is obtained.', 'DailyMed'),
